<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14049">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE:</b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/American%20Business.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8386">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8386 mb-requirement-id-8387">
        (a) Explain four features of the free enterprise system in the United
        States. Describe the difference between freedom and license. Tell how
        the Scout Oath and Scout Law apply to business and free enterprise.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/AvvPKwTpGqE" target="_blank"
          >What Is the Free Enterprise System? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/nKLUfmIcO5c" target="_blank"
          >What Is the Difference Between Freedom and Liberty (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8386 mb-requirement-id-8388">
        (b) Describe the Industrial Revolution and tell about the major
        developments that marked the start of the modern industrial era in the
        United States. Discuss three people who had a great influence on
        business or industry in the United States and describe what each did.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/FCpqN7GmLYk" target="_blank"
          >The Industrial Revolution: Crash Course History of Science #21
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/UPvwpYeOJnI" target="_blank"
          >Ford, Cars, and a New Revolution: Crash Course History of Science #28
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/vmbRtjN0gAk" target="_blank"
          >Man of Steel: Andrew Carnegie | The Gilded Age (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/wupQUvrmQjA" target="_blank"
          >Who Was: Henry Ford | Encyclopaedia Britannica (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/M9LnW09fvHE" target="_blank"
          >How JP Morgan Built It's Empire (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/tvXUHY4z0As" target="_blank"
          >Steve Jobs—Apple CEO (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8386 mb-requirement-id-8389">
        (c) Identify and describe to your counselor the five primary areas of
        business. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/_UaSu07bqNQ" target="_blank"
          >Functional Areas of a Business (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8386 mb-requirement-id-8413">
        (d) Explain the history of labor unions in the United States and the
        importance of labor unions and employers working together. Identify two
        major labor unions currently in existence. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ewu-v36szlE" target="_blank"
          >The Labor Movement in the United States | History (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.findlaw.com/employment/wages-and-benefits/list-of-us-labor-unions.html"
          target="_blank"
          >List of US Labor Unions (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8386 mb-requirement-id-8414">
        (e) Discuss with your counselor how business impacts the local,
        national, and global economy. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/SY3Z1WgqaYQ" target="_blank"
          >Small Businesses: Their Importance to the Global Economy (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8390">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8390 mb-requirement-id-8391">
        (a) Explain the three basic types of financial statements (income
        statement, balance sheet, and statement of cash flows). Discuss with
        your counselor how each statement can help business leaders make better
        decisions. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Fw14qE_9B-A" target="_blank"
          >4 Types of Financial Statements (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8390 mb-requirement-id-8392">
        (b) Explain how changes in interest rates, taxes, and government
        spending affect the flow of money into or out of business and industry.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/_etdZ9G8D4A" target="_blank"
          >How Interest Rates Affect Interest Rates, Financial Flows, and
          Exchange Rates (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8390 mb-requirement-id-8393">
        (c) Explain how a sole proprietorship, partnership, or limited liability
        company gets its capital. Discuss and explain four ways a corporation
        obtains capital. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/4-yE5JduTIo" target="_blank"
          >How To Choose the Right Business Structure: LLC vs Corporation vs
          Sole Proprietorship (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8390 mb-requirement-id-8394">
        (d) Name five kinds of insurance useful to business. Describe their
        purposes. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/O4AziG_UKl4" target="_blank"
          >5 Types of Insurance Your Business Needs (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8397">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8397 mb-requirement-id-8398">
        (a) Explain the place of profit in business. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/R8voRf5BjdA" target="_blank"
          >What Is Profit? (Gross Profit, Operating Profit, Net Income) | From a
          Business Professor (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8397 mb-requirement-id-8399">
        (b) Describe to your counselor green marketing and sustainable business
        practices. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/J9wzu_JeGyI" target="_blank"
          >What Is Eco Marketing or Green Marketing? | Needs and Significance of
          Eco Marketing (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8397 mb-requirement-id-8411">
        (c) Explain how ethics plays a role in business decision making.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/_zYVOnjLCR0" target="_blank"
          >Top 5 Business Ethics Lessons for Making the Right Decisions at Work
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8397 mb-requirement-id-8412">
        (d) Discuss the differences between operating a brick-and-mortar
        business versus an online business. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/PmIUu4a-N-I" target="_blank"
          >eCommerce vs Brick and Mortar Business (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8400">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Describe the role of the U.S. Department of Labor. Discuss TWO of the
      following topics with your counselor: Fair Labor Standards Act (FLSA),
      Occupational Safety and Health Act (OSHA), Family and Medical Leave Act
      (FMLA), or Employee Retirement Income Security Act (ERISA). <br /><i
        >Resources:</i
      >
      <a href="https://www.dol.gov/general/aboutdol/majorlaws" target="_blank"
        >Summary of the Major Laws of the Department of Labor (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/v9BhAWc-gWU" target="_blank"
        >What Is the Fair Labor Standards Act? (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/3JoXP3Gh9C8" target="_blank"
        >Intro to OSHA (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/K1KDFnCOLDY" target="_blank"
        >What's FMLA? FMLA Explained + What You Need To Know About FMLA
        (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/z8nq9iPIMk0" target="_blank"
        >What Is ERISA? Part 1 (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/f6QRobJIpWw" target="_blank"
        >What Is ERISA? Part 2 (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8404">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Choose a business and research how it applies to each of the primary areas
      of business (accounting, finance, economics, marketing, and management).
      Share what you have learned with your counselor.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-8407">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8407 mb-requirement-id-8408">
        (a) Choose one of the primary areas of business and identify three
        career opportunities. Select one and research the education, training,
        and experience required for this career. Discuss this with your
        counselor and explain why this interests you. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/wVfhXYdTcdQ" target="_blank"
          >Careers in Business (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/jMIa9SJiFb8" target="_blank"
          >Business Administration: A Complete Guide and Career Insight
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-8407 mb-requirement-id-8409">
        (b) Select a business leader and interview this individual to learn more
        about his or her company and career path. Discuss the role ethics plays
        in making business decisions. Share what you have learned with your
        counselor.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
</div>
